Dear Abinandan,

Thank you for the updated PR print and the Excel report. I have reviewed 
both outputs against the FSD requirements.

*QuestPDF and EPPlus — technology decision confirmed*

Both evaluations are accepted. *QuestPDF is confirmed as the SPINRISE 
standard for all transaction PDF prints. EPPlus is confirmed for all 
Excel and CSV data exports*. FastReports is not needed for Phase 1. The 
two-tool architecture —*QuestPDF for PDFs, EPPlus for Excel — is now the 
final decision for SPINRISE.
*
Your observation that QuestPDF layout design is time-consuming initially 
but straightforward and maintainable once done is the correct way to 
think about it. The initial investment in the QuestPDF C# template is a 
one-time cost per transaction print. Once the pattern is established for 
the PR print, *every subsequent print in the project follows the same 
structure.
*
*On the PR No. 329 print — three improvements, two corrections still needed*

Three improvements are clearly visible compared to the previous PR 368 
output. Drawing Number and Catalogue Number sub-rows are now present 
under every line item — this fulfils FSD Section 12 Rec 28. The Previous 
Purchase Date column is now populated correctly. Multi-page pagination 
is working — seven items across two pages renders cleanly.

*Two items still need attention before this print is production-ready.*

*First:* the ERP login username is still absent. FSD Section 12 Rec 17 
requires a 'Created By' field showing the ERP login user who typed the 
PR into the system (from PO_PRH.userId or createdby). This is separate 
from the Requester Name (KUMARESAN.V) which is already shown. Both must 
appear as labelled fields in the header. Add 'Created By: [ERP login 
username]' sourced from the API response.

*Second:* the 'Requested By' footer still shows 'Kalsofte' as hardcoded 
text. It was 'spinrise' in the previous version — the change shows 
progress but it must be a dynamic value from the data, not a company 
name. Replace with the actual Requester Name from the record — 
KUMARESAN.V in this case.

Also confirm: Item 2 (101B124 BELT) shows a blank in the App Cost Value 
column. The Previous Purchase Value of 26,004 is present but the App 
Cost column appears empty. Verify whether this is a data gap or a 
template mapping issue and fix accordingly.

*Alignment refinement is secondary to these content corrections — 
complete content first, then polish alignment.*

*Next step*

With the four FSD approvals now imminent and the technology stack 
confirmed, *your next priority is the first SPINRISE form development 
from an approved FSD*. Once M01 PR Form FSD receives CEO approval, you 
will have the locked baseline to begin React component and ASP.NET Core 
API development for the Purchase Requisition screen. *Prepare for that.*

Regards,
T. Mani

